  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Catholic Relief Services (CRS) is a leader in innovative humanitarian programming that helps people live to their full potential with dignity. For almost 70 years, CRS has delivered emergency relief and has sought solutions to poverty through community-based, sustainable development initiatives. CRS has been present in Burkina Faso since 1962, expanding its programs to provide long-term assistance in education, agriculture, health, HIV and AIDS programs, microfinance and peace and justice missions. Rise Against Hunger meals are distributed to extremely vulnerable individuals throughout more than 30 church centers on the territory of Burkina Faso. Within the same communities, CRS works to increase their resources and build long-term sustainability through programming contextualized to each community&apos;s needs.</narrative>
  </description>
